{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-15620/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-15620"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:56:20"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Woman pours water dramatically as man watches"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-15620","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-15620"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1/b45683d0-bc4f-4312-abdb-e84238f263ee","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:20:53.326Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While the scene parallels their first meeting, Alma is in bright green, the exact opposite of her <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW20185775 BCX4\" href=\"https://ptannotated.com/items/phan-01250.html\"><u>red waitress uniform</u></a>, signaling the complete transformation of her role. Although she is serving him food as she once did, she is no longer subservient to him. The food she gives him will poison him, weaking him so that he is reliant on her. She has finally truly escaped her role as the waitress and has become his equal.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1063.0397727272725,114.18211722488036,411.83612440191405,619.059509569378"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1/7e64f967-72f6-4ae8-a4eb-89e22fe83f2c","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:21:15.529Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>This scene in many respects parallels Reynolds and Alma’s <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW173800286 BCX4\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-01503.html\"><u>first meeting</u></a> at the café. She serves him a meal, indulging the “hungry boy” and his voracious appetite for both food and inuendo. She even pours water for him in the same way—with a long stream. This latter act, at least now when their relationship has developed further, is a power move meant to taunt Reynolds and annoy him as he dislikes unruly noises and distractions. It also precedes what is about to happen to him after he’s poisoned and must also pour out his insides.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15620/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:826.2178528708132,408.98325358851673,208.79784688995233,323.2962021531101"}}}]}]}]}